com.nokia.places

Interface ApiLink

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    Item, ItemPageLink, PlaceLink, SupplierLink

    public interface ApiLink
    This interface represents a Nokia Places link which requires another request to be made in order to retrieve the desired resource.

    Note: A link also contains metadata about the linked resource.


    See Also:
    Nokia's Restful Places API - Links

    • Method Summary

      Methods

    • Method Detail

      • getId

        java.lang.String getId()
        This method retrieves the unique identifier for the resource to which this ApiLink refers.

        Note: An identifier for a linked object is optional. A call to this method could return null.

        Returns:
        The linked object's identifier (could return null).

      • getTitle

        java.lang.String getTitle()
        This method retrieves the localized title for the resource to which this ApiLink refers. Client devices can display this title within an application.

        Note: A title for a linked object is optional. A call to this method could return null.

        Returns:
        The linked object's title (could return null).

      • getIcon

        javax.microedition.lcdui.Image getIcon()
        This method retrieves a link to the icon for the resource to which this ApiLink refers.

        Note: An icon for a linked object is optional. A call to this method could return null.

        Returns:
        The linked object's icon link (could return null).

      • getUri

        java.lang.String getUri()
        This method retrieves the URI of the RESTful Place Service which this link represents.
        Returns:
        The URL associated with this link.
